\@writefile{lot}{\contentsline {table}{\numberline {2}{\ignorespaces The 2x2 result: test BLEU on newstest2014; sacrebleu 13a, beam=5, length-penalty=1.0, 5-checkpoint averaged. Bold marks the better model within each row (capacity gap) and column (data-quality gap). The Big$-$Base difference flips sign: $+0.56$ on clean data, $-0.87$ on noisy data. Equivalently, the v1$\rightarrow $v2 quality drop is twice as large for Big ($-2.84$) as for Base ($-1.41$).}}{8}{table.caption.27}\protected@file@percent }
